  "prompt": "Have my wounds gone infected?",
  "response": "I'm not a doctor, but there are some signs you could look for to determine if a wound might be infected. Common signs of infection include:\n\n- Increased redness around the wound\n- Swelling or warmth in the area\n- Pus or drainage (which may be yellow, green, or foul-smelling)\n- Increased pain or tenderness\n- Fever or chills\n\nIf you notice any of these symptoms, it's important to consult with a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and treatment. They can provide the best advice based on your specific situation.",
